# Release Pipeline (Mac-driven, CI/CD does the build)

When the user asks to "release", "lançar release", "publicar release", "subir
versão" or anything semantically equivalent for this repo, follow this exact
flow. The Windows machine is NOT used; everything runs from the Mac via `gh`
CLI plus the GitHub Actions workflows in `.github/workflows/`.

## Hard rules (NEVER skip these)

- ALWAYS bump version in **all three** sources before tagging:
  - `src/Overtake.SimHub.Plugin/Properties/AssemblyInfo.cs` (`AssemblyVersion`
    + `AssemblyFileVersion`, both must match the new `X.Y.Z.0`).
  - `version.json` (`version: "X.Y.Z"`, `released: "<today>"`,
    `installerUrl` updated to the new tag).
  - `CHANGELOG.md` — add a `## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD` section with the new
    notes. `release.yml` refuses to release without this section.
- NEVER commit directly to `main` for code changes. Open a PR (workflow
  hotfixes inside `.github/workflows/*.yml` are the only OK exception, and
  only when needed to unstick a release that is already in flight).
- NEVER push a tag without CI green on the merged commit.
- NEVER amend / force-push the tag once `release.yml` has started. If the
  release fails, fix forward (re-run via `workflow_dispatch` with the same
  tag) or bump to the next patch version.
- ALWAYS use the inline author identity for git commits:
  `GIT_AUTHOR_NAME="drakokot" GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL="drakokot@gmail.com" GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="drakokot" GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="drakokot@gmail.com"`.
  The repo has no local `git config user.*` set — without these env vars,
  `git commit` aborts with "Author identity unknown".
- NEVER touch `git config`. NEVER use `git push --force` against `main` or
  any released tag.

## Step-by-step pipeline

### 1. Sanity-check the working state

```bash
cd /Users/wagner/Documents/plugin/overtake-simhub-plugin
git fetch --all --prune
git status -sb
git log -1 --oneline origin/main
gh auth status   # must show drakokot-oss with 'repo' AND 'workflow' scopes
```

If `gh auth status` is not authenticated, STOP and ask the user to run
`gh auth login` (HTTPS, browser flow). The pipeline cannot proceed without
this.

### 2. Bump the three version sources on a feature branch

```bash
git checkout main && git pull --ff-only
git checkout -b release/vX.Y.Z
```

Edit:
- `AssemblyInfo.cs`: both `AssemblyVersion` and `AssemblyFileVersion` to
  `"X.Y.Z.0"`.
- `version.json`: `version`, `released`, `installerUrl` (the URL must point
  at `Overtake.SimHub.Plugin-vX.Y.Z-Setup.exe`). Preserve `releaseNotes` if
  the user has already curated them; otherwise compose a short markdown
  summary.
- `CHANGELOG.md`: insert a new `## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD` block at the top
  (under the `# Changelog` header). Use the existing `### Fixed / ### Added
  / ### Changed` shape; mirror the `## [1.1.31]` block as a template.

When editing `AssemblyInfo.cs`, use ASCII characters only for
`AssemblyDescription` and `AssemblyCopyright`. Some editors mangle UTF-8
em-dashes (—) and the © symbol into multi-round mojibake (`ÃƒÆ’...`); we
already cleaned this once and don't want it back.

### 3. Open the PR

```bash
git add -A
GIT_AUTHOR_NAME="drakokot" GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL="drakokot@gmail.com" \
GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="drakokot" GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="drakokot@gmail.com" \
git commit -m "vX.Y.Z: <one-line summary>"
git push -u origin release/vX.Y.Z
gh pr create --base main --head release/vX.Y.Z \
  --title "vX.Y.Z: <one-line summary>" \
  --body "$(cat <<'EOF'
## Summary
<bullets matching CHANGELOG entry>

## Test plan
- [ ] CI green on Windows runner (build + Test-SessionStore + Test-Finalizer)
- [ ] After merge: tag vX.Y.Z fires release.yml -> .exe on Releases page
EOF
)"
```

### 4. Wait for CI to pass

```bash
gh pr checks <PR-NUMBER> --repo drakokot-oss/overtake-simhub-plugin
# Then watch the run id from the previous output:
gh run watch <RUN-ID> --repo drakokot-oss/overtake-simhub-plugin --exit-status
```

Expected duration: ~3 minutes (cache warm) or ~10 minutes (cache cold —
SimHub portable + ConfuserEx download). Test counts must end with
`PASS: 67   FAIL: 0` (SessionStore) and `PASS: 91   FAIL: 0` (Finalizer,
or higher; Test 17 added 5+ new asserts).

If CI fails, STOP. Investigate the logs:
```bash
gh run view <RUN-ID> --repo drakokot-oss/overtake-simhub-plugin --log-failed
```

### 5. Squash-merge the PR

```bash
gh pr merge <PR-NUMBER> --repo drakokot-oss/overtake-simhub-plugin \
  --squash --delete-branch \
  --subject "vX.Y.Z: <one-line summary> (#<PR-NUMBER>)" \
  --body "Squash of N commits. See PR #<PR-NUMBER>."
```

### 6. Tag and push (this fires release.yml)

```bash
git checkout main && git pull --ff-only
GIT_AUTHOR_NAME="drakokot" GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL="drakokot@gmail.com" \
GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="drakokot" GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="drakokot@gmail.com" \
git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "Release vX.Y.Z

<short summary>"
git push origin vX.Y.Z
```

### 7. Watch release.yml

```bash
gh run list --repo drakokot-oss/overtake-simhub-plugin --workflow release.yml --limit 1
gh run watch <RUN-ID> --repo drakokot-oss/overtake-simhub-plugin --exit-status
```

Expected duration: ~5–10 min. The pipeline does: verify versions, build
(Release), tests, ConfuserEx (silent install of SimHub via Inno Setup,
stage SimHub refs into bin\Release for dnlib resolution, ignore
Confuser.CLI's post-obfuscation `Console.ReadKey` exit code, assert success
by output DLL presence), Inno Setup compile, GitHub Release upload.

If `release.yml` fails AFTER the commit/tag are already pushed, prefer to
fix forward by editing `.github/workflows/release.yml` on `main` and
re-running with the SAME tag via:
```bash
gh workflow run release.yml --repo drakokot-oss/overtake-simhub-plugin \
  --ref main -f tag=vX.Y.Z
```

The `workflow_dispatch` always reads the YAML from `main` (so your fix
applies) but checks out the repo at the tag (so the source the .exe is
built from stays exactly what was reviewed).

### 8. Verify the public artifacts

```bash
gh release view vX.Y.Z --repo drakokot-oss/overtake-simhub-plugin \
  --json name,tagName,publishedAt,url,assets
curl -sIL https://github.com/drakokot-oss/overtake-simhub-plugin/releases/download/vX.Y.Z/Overtake.SimHub.Plugin-vX.Y.Z-Setup.exe \
  | grep -E '^(HTTP|Content-Length|Location)'
curl -s https://raw.githubusercontent.com/drakokot-oss/overtake-simhub-plugin/main/version.json \
  | head -3
```

Expected: HTTP/2 302 (asset redirect) -> HTTP/2 200 (S3), Content-Length
~2.3 MB, and `version.json` on `main` shows `"version": "X.Y.Z"`.

### 9. Report back to the user

Include in the final reply:
- Release URL: `https://github.com/drakokot-oss/overtake-simhub-plugin/releases/tag/vX.Y.Z`
- Installer URL: `https://github.com/drakokot-oss/overtake-simhub-plugin/releases/download/vX.Y.Z/Overtake.SimHub.Plugin-vX.Y.Z-Setup.exe`
- Installer size + SHA256 (from the asset metadata).
- Confirmation that the in-plugin auto-updater will detect the new version
  on the user's installations.

## Failure-mode crib sheet

These are the ones we have already debugged once. If they reappear, fix
the same way without re-debugging from scratch.

- **`Specified cast is not valid` in export pipeline** -> always Box int
  via `(object)(int)dr.GridPosition`, never `(object)dr.GridPosition` for
  byte fields. Defensive readers in `ComputeAwards` and
  `ComputeMostConsistent` use `Convert.ToInt32(...)`. Test 17 enforces
  this; if it fails, look there first.
- **CI `SimHub.Plugins.dll not found`** -> the SHWotever ZIP wraps an Inno
  Setup `.exe`, not a portable layout. The workflows already silent-install
  it; check the cache key isn't stale.
- **CI `dnlib.AssemblyResolveException` in ConfuserEx** -> SimHub refs not
  staged. The release workflow copies them into `bin\Release` before
  Confuser; check that block didn't get removed.
- **CI `& was unexpected at this time`** -> someone tried to invoke
  Confuser via `cmd /c "&"`. Use `Start-Process` instead.
- **CI `Cannot read keys when ... console input has been redirected`** ->
  Confuser's `Console.ReadKey` after success. The workflow already ignores
  the post-obfuscation exit code and asserts by output DLL presence.
- **`fatal: unable to auto-detect email address`** -> always pass
  `GIT_AUTHOR_NAME / GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL / GIT_COMMITTER_NAME / GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL`
  inline. Do not modify `git config`.
- **PowerShell scripts failing with `Missing closing '}' / The string is
  missing the terminator`** -> Unicode em-dashes/smart-quotes in `.ps1`
  files. PS 5.1 on Windows mangles them. Replace with ASCII (`-`, `'`,
  `"`, `...`, `->`).

## When NOT to follow this pipeline

- Workflow file edits (`.github/workflows/*.yml`) intended to unstick an
  already-tagged release: those go directly to `main` (commit + push)
  followed by `gh workflow run release.yml -f tag=vX.Y.Z`. No PR needed,
  but document the change clearly in the commit message.
- Hot patches that bypass tests: do NOT do this. Always require CI green.
